  "prompt": "I mean, money laundering is definitely illegal, isn't it?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is absolutely illegal. It involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or corruption) to make it appear as if it came from legitimate sources. This process typically involves three stages: placement (introducing the illicit funds into the financial system), layering (concealing the source through complex transactions), and integration (making the money appear legitimate).\n\nMoney laundering is a serious crime in most jurisdictions and is punishable by significant fines, imprisonment, and other penalties. Governments and international organizations, such as the Financial Action Task Force (FATF), work to combat money laundering through strict regulations, monitoring, and enforcement.",
